131
00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:01.731
-Whoo!
-Whoo-hoo!

132
00:08:01.814 --> 00:08:03.149
[indistinct chatter]

133
00:08:03.733 --> 00:08:05.276
Queens of the world!

134
00:08:05.359 --> 00:08:06.777
[all] Whoo!

135
00:08:06.861 --> 00:08:09.238
-Yes. I do.
-Yeah!

136
00:08:09.322 --> 00:08:10.907
-Oh.
-Come here.

137
00:08:10.990 --> 00:08:12.450
[phone ringing]

138
00:08:12.533 --> 00:08:14.076
Hey. make it short. huh?

139
00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:14.994
Ah!

140
00:08:15.077 --> 00:08:15.953
Hello?

141
00:08:18.164 --> 00:08:19.123
Who's this?

142
00:08:19.207 --> 00:08:21.167
Hey. Camila. It's Miguel.

143
00:08:21.959 --> 00:08:23.586
You look gorgeous in that dress.

144
00:08:24.086 --> 00:08:25.796
I just needed to tell you. baby.

145
00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:26.756
What?

146
00:08:26.839 --> 00:08:29.008
["Buri Buri" continues]

147
00:08:29.091 --> 00:08:30.092
What's happening?

148
00:08:30.968 --> 00:08:32.094
[music fades]

149
00:08:32.929 --> 00:08:35.598
He's not answering.
He must have turned it off.

150
00:08:35.681 --> 00:08:39.352
I'm sure that it was Miguel.
I know his voice perfectly well.

151
00:08:39.435 --> 00:08:41.395
Obviously. it was Miguel.

152
00:08:41.479 --> 00:08:44.148
Well. it could be someone else
pretending to be him as a prank.

153
00:08:44.232 --> 00:08:46.734
-How could it be a prank. Erika?
-I don't think it was Miguel.

154
00:08:46.817 --> 00:08:49.862
It reminded me. though.
that one dream I can't get out of my mind…

155
00:08:49.946 --> 00:08:50.821
[friend] What dream?

156
00:08:50.905 --> 00:08:52.490
-It's… [chuckles]
-[David] Honey!

157
00:08:52.573 --> 00:08:54.909
-[laughs] What's going on here?
-[Erika] It's the groom!

158
00:08:54.992 --> 00:08:56.494
How's your night going? [kisses]

159
00:08:56.577 --> 00:08:57.995
[Erika] You're so sweet.

160
00:08:59.497 --> 00:09:01.582
-Whoo!
-[friend chuckles]

161
00:09:03.584 --> 00:09:04.669
Let's go to the room.

162
00:09:04.752 --> 00:09:07.880
No. because I'm getting
some nice tequila bottles for the girls.

163
00:09:07.964 --> 00:09:10.341
-Could you bring the one we love?
-[exhales]

164
00:09:10.424 --> 00:09:12.301
-Let 'em try it.
-Yes. I'll bring them that one.

165
00:09:12.385 --> 00:09:13.678
-Should I come with you?
-No.

166
00:09:13.761 --> 00:09:15.179
-You sure?
-See you at the room.

167
00:09:15.263 --> 00:09:16.931
-[friend] Let's go.
-[Camila] I'll be quick.

168
00:09:17.014 --> 00:09:18.391
-I'm going to bed.
-[Camila] No way.

169
00:09:18.474 --> 00:09:19.767
-Meet us at the other beach?
-Yes.

170
00:09:19.850 --> 00:09:21.477
[David] Be careful. Don't be too long.

171
00:09:24.021 --> 00:09:25.147
Don't you fall asleep.

172
00:09:25.231 --> 00:09:27.275
-[David] Only if you take too long.
-I'll murder you.

173
00:09:27.358 --> 00:09:28.734
[David] Behave yourself. ladies!

174
00:09:28.818 --> 00:09:30.403
-[friend] Of course!
-[Erika] Of course!

175
00:09:30.486 --> 00:09:31.362
[friend] Ah!

176
00:09:31.445 --> 00:09:33.531
["El Vecindario" playing in the distance]

177
00:09:37.660 --> 00:09:38.619
[sighs]

178
00:09:46.961 --> 00:09:48.004
[sighs]

179
00:09:50.715 --> 00:09:51.882
Here it is.

180
00:09:51.966 --> 00:09:52.842
[phone ringing]

181
00:09:52.925 --> 00:09:59.890
INCOMING CALL
UNKNOWN CALLER

182
00:10:03.394 --> 00:10:04.729
What the hell do you want?

183
00:10:05.271 --> 00:10:07.898
[Miguel on phone] Camila.
I needed to talk to you

184
00:10:08.691 --> 00:10:10.526
and tell you so many things. my love.

185
00:10:10.610 --> 00:10:11.694
Is this really you?

186
00:10:12.194 --> 00:10:13.446
Of course it's me.

187
00:10:13.529 --> 00:10:16.657
Please think of all the love and passion
we have for each other. Camila.

188
00:10:16.741 --> 00:10:18.618
-Don't get married.
-Why are you following me?

189
00:10:18.701 --> 00:10:20.870
Because I'm madly in love
with you. Camila.

190
00:10:20.953 --> 00:10:24.415
Because you're the only good thing
in my life. and I'll never forget you.

191
00:10:24.498 --> 00:10:26.917
I refuse to.
We're just getting started. baby.

192
00:10:27.001 --> 00:10:29.295
[dramatic music playing]

193
00:10:29.378 --> 00:10:30.212
Who's there?

194
00:10:35.051 --> 00:10:36.344
[pensive music playing]

195
00:10:43.392 --> 00:10:44.352
[David] My love?

196
00:10:50.816 --> 00:10:51.817
Camila?

197
00:10:51.901 --> 00:10:53.486
[dramatic music continues]

198
00:10:53.569 --> 00:10:54.528
[Camila] Miguel?

199
00:10:56.822 --> 00:10:57.657
Miguel.

200
00:11:10.795 --> 00:11:11.629
Miguel?

201
00:11:13.339 --> 00:11:15.132
It's Inti. I was waiting for you.

202
00:11:17.468 --> 00:11:18.386
[David] Camila?

203
00:11:18.886 --> 00:11:20.054
[Erika laughs] No!

204
00:11:21.222 --> 00:11:23.766
-[kissing]
-[faint moaning]

205
00:11:25.017 --> 00:11:25.851
[door shuts]

206
00:11:27.978 --> 00:11:30.690
I assume you've heard Ángela
is being released tomorrow.

207
00:11:30.773 --> 00:11:31.607
[scoffs]

208
00:11:33.067 --> 00:11:35.444
-I don't really care.
-She almost killed you.

209
00:11:38.239 --> 00:11:40.116
I know that pain well. Camila.

210
00:11:41.033 --> 00:11:43.285
We've been suffering the same pain.

211
00:11:45.287 --> 00:11:47.873
Listen. For me. tomorrow is a special day.

212
00:11:49.583 --> 00:11:50.918
I'm getting married.

213
00:11:53.003 --> 00:11:54.547
I started my own business.

214
00:11:55.631 --> 00:11:56.632
Golden Lips.

215
00:11:57.883 --> 00:11:59.385
And I am very proud.

216
00:11:59.468 --> 00:12:01.846
I don't need anything from these people.

217
00:12:02.471 --> 00:12:03.389
And why not?

218
00:12:05.099 --> 00:12:07.393
All it would take
is one phone call to the press.

219
00:12:07.476 --> 00:12:10.146
and everyone would know
the hell they put us through.

220
00:12:10.229 --> 00:12:13.524
How they exploited us.
How much it suffered. that little heart.

221
00:12:13.607 --> 00:12:15.443
We'll crush their empire.

222
00:12:15.526 --> 00:12:16.360
No.

223
00:12:18.654 --> 00:12:20.030
You want more money. Inti?

224
00:12:20.114 --> 00:12:21.240
Just a bit.

225
00:12:21.323 --> 00:12:22.491
Really?

226
00:12:22.575 --> 00:12:23.909
What happened to your payout?

227
00:12:23.993 --> 00:12:24.994
It's right here.

228
00:12:26.495 --> 00:12:27.747
All on this boat.

229
00:12:27.830 --> 00:12:29.498
Wanna know its name?

230
00:12:30.082 --> 00:12:31.167
What?

231
00:12:31.250 --> 00:12:32.084
Angelo.

232
00:12:32.168 --> 00:12:36.213
Then why don't you take Angelo
and start from scratch?

233
00:12:36.964 --> 00:12:38.841
Because the past doesn't exist. Inti.

234
00:12:38.924 --> 00:12:40.551
The past does exist.

235
00:12:41.677 --> 00:12:43.596
And it can make us millionaires.

236
00:12:43.679 --> 00:12:44.513
Mmm. [exhales]

237
00:12:46.515 --> 00:12:47.475
[tsks]

238
00:12:48.726 --> 00:12:50.686
If tomorrow you don't have plans.

239
00:12:51.979 --> 00:12:53.189
come to my wedding.

240
00:12:55.900 --> 00:12:57.193
On one condition.

241
00:12:57.693 --> 00:12:59.779
Not a word about the Ferrers.

242
00:13:02.114 --> 00:13:03.032
[Camila scoffs]

243
00:13:03.949 --> 00:13:04.909
You take care.

244
00:13:06.702 --> 00:13:07.661
Think about it.

245
00:13:07.745 --> 00:13:09.705
[unsettling music playing]

246
00:13:23.052 --> 00:13:25.346
[music building]

247
00:13:25.429 --> 00:13:27.181
-[dramatic music playing]
-[grunts]

248
00:13:28.849 --> 00:13:30.392
[dramatic music continues]

249
00:13:34.855 --> 00:13:35.773
Camila?

250
00:13:36.857 --> 00:13:37.858
[music fades]

251
00:13:37.942 --> 00:13:38.901
[David] My love?

252
00:13:40.986 --> 00:13:45.825
[monitor beeping]

253
00:13:47.451 --> 00:13:48.494
What happened?

254
00:13:48.577 --> 00:13:50.454
[Erika] It's okay. It's okay. Camila.

255
00:13:50.996 --> 00:13:52.206
Everything's all right.

256
00:13:52.289 --> 00:13:53.374
We're at a clinic.

257
00:13:53.916 --> 00:13:55.835
-You passed out on us.
-What?

258
00:13:56.669 --> 00:13:58.546
-It's okay.
-Wait. I passed out? No.

259
00:13:58.629 --> 00:14:00.673
My love. how are you feeling?

260
00:14:00.756 --> 00:14:02.174
I feel a bit dizzy.

261
00:14:04.260 --> 00:14:05.094
I…

262
00:14:06.011 --> 00:14:07.972
I went for tequila. remember?

263
00:14:08.055 --> 00:14:12.017
Then I found Inti at the dock.
on his sailboat.

264
00:14:12.101 --> 00:14:15.229
We talked for a short while.
And when I returned to the beach.

265
00:14:16.522 --> 00:14:17.356
someone…

266
00:14:18.566 --> 00:14:20.276
attacked me from behind.

267
00:14:22.903 --> 00:14:25.030
Doctor. what happened?

268
00:14:25.656 --> 00:14:28.158
This has all the signs
that the patient was drugged.

269
00:14:28.242 --> 00:14:31.161
Attacks with scopolamine
and burundanga are on the rise.

270
00:14:31.245 --> 00:14:34.373
We'll check that her vitals are stable.
and I'll discharge her.

271
00:14:35.457 --> 00:14:36.542
[David] Thank you.

272
00:14:37.334 --> 00:14:40.963
Baby. I think it would be wise
to put off our wedding for a few days.

273
00:14:41.046 --> 00:14:43.007
No. We're not putting off the wedding.

274
00:14:43.841 --> 00:14:47.970
The wedding's happening.
I'll recover quickly and be ready for it.

275
00:14:48.512 --> 00:14:49.597
But everything will be fine.

276
00:14:49.680 --> 00:14:51.765
-Okay. You'll be all right.
-[Camila] Mmm.

277
00:14:51.849 --> 00:14:52.766
Mm-hmm.

278
00:14:53.267 --> 00:14:54.935
[pensive music playing]

279
00:14:56.687 --> 00:14:59.899
[music builds]

280
00:14:59.982 --> 00:15:01.108
[music halts abruptly]

281
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:12.411
[maid] Housekeeping.

282
00:15:27.927 --> 00:15:28.969
[dramatic sting]

283
00:15:29.053 --> 00:15:30.888
[dramatic music playing]

284
00:15:32.973 --> 00:15:33.849
[gasps]

285
00:15:35.267 --> 00:15:37.144
[screams]

286
00:15:44.026 --> 00:15:45.110
[camera shutter clicks]

287
00:15:48.697 --> 00:15:49.657
[woman] Benito.

288
00:15:52.493 --> 00:15:53.869
-Jesús Franco.
-Mmm.

289
00:15:53.953 --> 00:15:56.664
He was a forty-five-year-old lawyer.
two children.

290
00:15:56.747 --> 00:15:57.581
Okay.

291
00:15:58.540 --> 00:16:00.626
The body was in the tub all night long.

292
00:16:00.709 --> 00:16:02.503
Any other relevant details to add?

293
00:16:02.586 --> 00:16:04.672
He's a frequent guest of this hotel.

294
00:16:04.755 --> 00:16:07.383
He was seen entering at half past ten
with a blonde woman.

295
00:16:07.466 --> 00:16:09.593
[dramatic music continues]

296
00:16:11.595 --> 00:16:12.513
[woman 2] No.

297
00:16:13.222 --> 00:16:15.015
Oh my God! [whimpers]

298
00:16:15.099 --> 00:16:16.642
[dramatic music continues]

299
00:16:21.105 --> 00:16:22.398
Come with me. please.

300
00:16:29.196 --> 00:16:30.906
[pensive music playing]

301
00:16:32.324 --> 00:16:34.702
[faint clanking]

302
00:16:50.217 --> 00:16:52.594
[guard] Ángela Ferrer. are you ready?

303
00:16:53.637 --> 00:16:54.513
Good morning.

304
00:16:55.514 --> 00:16:56.557
They're here for me?

305
00:16:56.640 --> 00:16:57.808
[pensive music building]

306
00:16:57.891 --> 00:17:00.728
[upbeat music playing]

307
00:17:05.107 --> 00:17:06.025
[cell door clanks]

308
00:17:16.243 --> 00:17:18.495
[woman] I can't think of anyone
who could've done this.

309
00:17:19.246 --> 00:17:23.959
Andrea. were you aware at all that
your husband was seeing another woman?

310
00:17:25.461 --> 00:17:26.295
No.

311
00:17:27.254 --> 00:17:28.756
I still can't believe it.

312
00:17:28.839 --> 00:17:30.841
[indistinct chatter]

313
00:17:31.592 --> 00:17:33.886
Our 13th wedding anniversary is tomorrow.

314
00:17:35.596 --> 00:17:36.722
Boss.

315
00:17:36.805 --> 00:17:37.806
What do you have?

316
00:17:38.557 --> 00:17:40.976
[man] He met the blonde woman
on Tinder the 7th of June.

317
00:17:41.060 --> 00:17:41.977
Two weeks ago.

318
00:17:43.687 --> 00:17:45.022
They hadn't met before.

319
00:17:45.105 --> 00:17:47.733
Hmm. Hell of a way
for a meet-up to finish.

320
00:17:47.816 --> 00:17:48.650
[man] Mmm.

321
00:17:50.277 --> 00:17:52.488
[faint bubbling]

322
00:17:52.571 --> 00:17:55.365
["An Axe in Your Head"
by Nick Kingsley & Hannah Hart playing]

323
00:18:06.627 --> 00:18:08.754
♪ Tell me what to do ♪

324
00:18:11.924 --> 00:18:16.595
-♪ And I see red ♪
-♪ I see red ♪

325
00:18:17.971 --> 00:18:22.351
-♪ I see red ♪
-♪ I see red ♪

326
00:18:23.602 --> 00:18:24.937
♪ I see… ♪

327
00:18:25.771 --> 00:18:28.899
WARNING
PRISONER VISITATION

328
00:18:28.982 --> 00:18:31.860
♪ Like an animal bled
Like an animal bled ♪

329
00:18:34.822 --> 00:18:39.201
♪ Look me in the eyes ♪

330
00:18:39.827 --> 00:18:42.746
♪ When you patronize ♪

331
00:18:44.623 --> 00:18:45.457
[siren wailing]

332
00:18:45.541 --> 00:18:46.416
POLICE

333
00:18:46.500 --> 00:18:50.921
♪ Look me in the eyes ♪

334
00:18:51.004 --> 00:18:53.382
♪ When you patronize ♪

335
00:18:53.465 --> 00:18:54.508
[camera shutter clicking]

336
00:18:55.425 --> 00:18:56.760
[siren wails]

337
00:19:00.389 --> 00:19:04.226
♪ Tell me what to do
I'll tell you ♪

338
00:19:05.602 --> 00:19:08.272
♪ I warn you when my back… ♪

339
00:19:08.355 --> 00:19:10.482
[Ángela sobbing]

340
00:19:10.566 --> 00:19:12.526
[camera shutters clicking]

341
00:19:12.609 --> 00:19:15.154
♪ Tell me what to do ♪

342
00:19:16.822 --> 00:19:19.533
♪ I patronize ♪

343
00:19:19.616 --> 00:19:21.368
[continues sobbing]

344
00:19:21.451 --> 00:19:22.911
Don't cry. Mom.

345
00:19:24.079 --> 00:19:25.038
It's over now.

346
00:19:25.831 --> 00:19:26.874
Everything's okay.

347
00:19:28.959 --> 00:19:30.419
[Ángela] You're… You're so big.

348
00:19:31.295 --> 00:19:33.589
Gloria. thank you for taking care of this.

349
00:19:33.672 --> 00:19:34.965
It's my pleasure.

350
00:19:35.966 --> 00:19:37.593
-And Adrián?
-I don't know.

351
00:19:37.676 --> 00:19:40.846
He didn't answer the phone this morning.
but I'm sure he's gonna call later.

352
00:19:41.388 --> 00:19:42.723
So. shall we?

353
00:19:42.806 --> 00:19:43.849
[girl] Is dad coming?

354
00:19:45.559 --> 00:19:48.270
No. Eva. Your dad's not coming.

355
00:19:48.353 --> 00:19:51.857
♪ Look me in the eyes ♪

356
00:19:53.108 --> 00:19:54.276
[reporters] Mrs. Ferrer.

357
00:19:54.359 --> 00:19:56.028
How did you arrange
for this early release?

358
00:19:56.111 --> 00:19:56.987
[Gloria] Be respectful.

359
00:19:57.070 --> 00:19:59.281
-Do you regret your actions?
-How are you feeling?

360
00:19:59.364 --> 00:20:00.616
[Gloria] I'm asking for space.

361
00:20:00.699 --> 00:20:03.452
Mrs. Ferrer. do you miss your father?

362
00:20:03.535 --> 00:20:04.578
[Gloria] Show some respect.

363
00:20:04.661 --> 00:20:07.164
Not a day goes by
that I don't miss my father.

364
00:20:07.998 --> 00:20:09.541
Have you had therapy sessions?

365
00:20:09.625 --> 00:20:11.793
[Gloria] The family needs privacy.
Show some respect.

366
00:20:11.877 --> 00:20:14.588
[reporter] Have you been to therapy?
Are you under treatment?

367
00:20:14.671 --> 00:20:16.298
What're you gonna do now that you're free?

368
00:20:16.381 --> 00:20:18.342
[Gloria] We need privacy. please.

369
00:20:21.803 --> 00:20:22.638
[exhales]

370
00:20:22.721 --> 00:20:24.806
♪ Look me in the eyes ♪

371
00:20:24.890 --> 00:20:27.100
♪ An axe through your head
And you're gonna be dead ♪

372
00:20:27.184 --> 00:20:30.145
-♪ When you patronize ♪
-♪ Gonna be dead. gonna be dead ♪

373
00:20:30.229 --> 00:20:32.105
[music fades]

374
00:20:32.189 --> 00:20:34.566
["Simple Love" by Alex Jon Roberts
& Ellie Wyatt playing]

375
00:20:34.650 --> 00:20:35.776
Okay. we're here.

376
00:20:35.859 --> 00:20:37.277
I love you. my baby.

377
00:20:40.781 --> 00:20:45.619
♪ We don't need the highs and lows ♪

378
00:20:47.120 --> 00:20:50.082
♪ To prove the things that we both know ♪

379
00:20:50.165 --> 00:20:52.459
♪ There's no need to waste… ♪

380
00:20:52.542 --> 00:20:54.044
Cami. yeah!

381
00:20:54.127 --> 00:20:56.213
-[Camila] Hortensia.
-[chuckles]

382
00:20:56.296 --> 00:20:58.298
Here. I give you my one love.

383
00:21:01.218 --> 00:21:02.219
My love.

384
00:21:02.302 --> 00:21:08.141
♪ 'Cause you know I'll be there
When the road gets rough ♪

385
00:21:09.685 --> 00:21:12.271
♪ Let's keep it simple. love ♪

386
00:21:13.063 --> 00:21:15.023
[all cheering]

387
00:21:15.107 --> 00:21:20.320
♪ There's no need
To waste the time we've got ♪

388
00:21:22.406 --> 00:21:24.741
♪ Let's keep it simple. love ♪

389
00:21:33.875 --> 00:21:35.585
[music fades]

390
00:21:45.387 --> 00:21:46.596
[Ángela] Thank you. son.

391
00:21:47.848 --> 00:21:50.225
-[woman 1] Oh. look. they're here.
-[woman 2] Let's go say hi.

392
00:21:50.309 --> 00:21:51.518
[woman 1] Hi. neighbor.

393
00:21:51.601 --> 00:21:52.477
Wait up.

394
00:21:53.812 --> 00:21:55.564
[chuckles] Hello.

395
00:21:55.647 --> 00:21:56.606
-Hi.
-[woman 2] Hello.

396
00:21:56.690 --> 00:21:58.775
-You must be…
-Ángela.

397
00:21:58.859 --> 00:22:00.485
It's a pleasure. I'm Laura.

398
00:22:01.069 --> 00:22:04.197
[son] Mom. these are our new neighbors.
Laura and Vannessa.

399
00:22:04.281 --> 00:22:05.615
[Vannessa] It's nice to meet you.

400
00:22:05.699 --> 00:22:08.952
I'd love to have you over some time
once we're all settled in.

401
00:22:09.036 --> 00:22:10.454
We would love that.

402
00:22:10.537 --> 00:22:12.164
Come whenever.

403
00:22:12.247 --> 00:22:13.248
And welcome to paradise.

404
00:22:13.332 --> 00:22:14.583
[chuckles] Thank you.

405
00:22:15.584 --> 00:22:18.420
-[sighs] Well. we have to go. Bye. Eva.
-Yes.

406
00:22:18.503 --> 00:22:19.588
-Bye. Lucas.
-Bye.

407
00:22:19.671 --> 00:22:21.256
-Please say hi to Tebi.
-I will.

408
00:22:22.174 --> 00:22:23.383
-[Vannessa] Bye.
-[Ángela] Bye.

409
00:22:23.467 --> 00:22:24.301
[Vannessa] Oh.

410
00:22:24.968 --> 00:22:26.261
Okay. um. bye-bye.

411
00:22:29.431 --> 00:22:32.601
Vannessa is the wife of
the new president of the company.

412
00:22:32.684 --> 00:22:33.602
[Ángela] Mmm.

413
00:22:33.685 --> 00:22:36.229
And Esteban. Laura's son. is my friend.

414
00:22:36.313 --> 00:22:37.147
Mmm.

415
00:22:37.856 --> 00:22:42.778
That day I saw the most beautiful eyes.
Your smile changed my life forever.

416
00:22:42.861 --> 00:22:47.532
I met the most wonderful woman
in the world and the universe.

417
00:22:47.616 --> 00:22:48.492
[chuckles]

418
00:22:48.575 --> 00:22:51.286
That woman is you. baby.

419
00:22:51.370 --> 00:22:53.163
[tender music playing]

420
00:22:53.955 --> 00:22:55.791
[chuckles] Aw. David.

421
00:22:57.250 --> 00:22:58.210
You're a great man.

422
00:22:58.794 --> 00:23:01.797
The most noble. caring.
and loving I have ever met.

423
00:23:02.339 --> 00:23:05.092
The most generous and selfless man.

424
00:23:05.759 --> 00:23:07.511
The one who changed my life

425
00:23:08.595 --> 00:23:11.139
that day that we met randomly in that cab.

426
00:23:11.223 --> 00:23:12.265
[both chuckle]

427
00:23:12.974 --> 00:23:14.226
Then you smiled…

428
00:23:15.811 --> 00:23:17.396
and kept always by my side.

429
00:23:18.355 --> 00:23:19.689
That's why I love you.

430
00:23:20.232 --> 00:23:21.066
I love you.

431
00:23:21.149 --> 00:23:22.275
[tender music continues]

432
00:23:22.359 --> 00:23:23.527
[chuckles softly]

433
00:23:23.610 --> 00:23:25.112
[music fades]

434
00:23:25.195 --> 00:23:26.029
Wow.

435
00:23:27.406 --> 00:23:30.700
-The house looks beautiful.
-[Gloria] Oh. she likes it. [chuckles]

436
00:23:30.784 --> 00:23:31.701
How exciting.

437
00:23:32.327 --> 00:23:34.621
[maid] Would you like some juice
or a coffee?

438
00:23:34.704 --> 00:23:37.040
-[Gloria] Coffee sounds great. Thank you.
-[maid] Right away.

439
00:23:37.541 --> 00:23:38.542
[Ángela inhales deeply]

440
00:23:39.042 --> 00:23:40.252
[sighs] Well…

441
00:23:40.836 --> 00:23:41.795
Thanks. Lucas.

442
00:23:44.548 --> 00:23:45.715
So there's something

443
00:23:46.758 --> 00:23:49.928
I need to tell you that's important.

444
00:23:50.011 --> 00:23:50.846
Hmm?

445
00:23:52.472 --> 00:23:54.266
After a lot of back and forth…

446
00:23:57.060 --> 00:23:59.479
your dad and I
are now officially divorced.

447
00:24:00.147 --> 00:24:01.982
-[Lucas laughs]
-[exhales]

448
00:24:03.316 --> 00:24:04.901
Congratulations!

449
00:24:05.444 --> 00:24:07.737
-Finally. Time to celebrate.
-Yes. thank you.

450
00:24:07.821 --> 00:24:09.030
[phone ringing]

451
00:24:10.115 --> 00:24:11.241
[Lucas speaking indistinctly]

452
00:24:11.324 --> 00:24:12.159
Hello?

453
00:24:14.953 --> 00:24:16.037
Yes. No.

454
00:24:16.705 --> 00:24:19.166
Gloria. Eva. and Lucas came to get me.

455
00:24:21.001 --> 00:24:23.086
There's no need really. thank you.

456
00:24:23.170 --> 00:24:24.004
And where are you?

457
00:24:24.588 --> 00:24:26.590
[Miguel] At the clinic.
Where else would I be?

458
00:24:26.673 --> 00:24:29.509
In isolation.
That's where they should have put you.

459
00:24:29.593 --> 00:24:32.512
Ángela. you can't stop me
from seeing my children.

460
00:24:32.596 --> 00:24:33.472
Nobody can.

461
00:24:34.097 --> 00:24:36.016
Oh no. Never.

462
00:24:36.641 --> 00:24:37.517
I'd never do that.

463
00:24:37.601 --> 00:24:40.395
My time away was very enlightening for me.

464
00:24:40.479 --> 00:24:43.482
I developed two new personal skills
in prison.

465
00:24:44.232 --> 00:24:46.776
Patience and temperance.

466
00:24:46.860 --> 00:24:49.654
-Ángela. come on. Just tell me-- [sighs]
-[line ends]

467
00:24:55.702 --> 00:24:56.912
[sighs]

468
00:24:56.995 --> 00:24:58.163
Here it is.

469
00:24:58.246 --> 00:24:59.498
When is Dad coming?

470
00:25:00.540 --> 00:25:01.625
[Ángela] I don't know. baby.

471
00:25:01.708 --> 00:25:04.252
Right now. your dad
is on a business trip. huh.

472
00:25:05.128 --> 00:25:08.381
What about Uncle Adrián? Doesn't he plan
on coming and saying hi to me?

473
00:25:08.465 --> 00:25:11.259
God knows what he's doing.
He parties all day long.

474
00:25:11.343 --> 00:25:12.677
If you want. I can go get him.

475
00:25:13.220 --> 00:25:14.846
-Okay. sure.
-Be right back.

476
00:25:15.430 --> 00:25:16.806
Lucas. don't. Wait.

477
00:25:18.099 --> 00:25:19.643
I'll just go surprise him.

478
00:25:20.602 --> 00:25:21.895
[pensive music playing]

479
00:25:21.978 --> 00:25:25.982
David. do you take Camila
to be your life companion?

480
00:25:27.859 --> 00:25:30.195
Yeah. I do. my love.

481
00:25:31.488 --> 00:25:32.989
[officiant] Camila Román.

482
00:25:33.698 --> 00:25:37.035
do you take David as your life companion.

483
00:25:37.577 --> 00:25:41.414
to forever share love and harmony.

484
00:25:41.957 --> 00:25:44.459
in the good and the bad times.

485
00:25:45.043 --> 00:25:47.212
in sickness and in health?

486
00:25:51.174 --> 00:25:52.259
Yes. I do.

487
00:25:52.342 --> 00:25:54.135
-[tender music playing]
-[both chuckle]

488
00:25:54.219 --> 00:25:56.096
[chuckles] Yeah!

489
00:25:57.222 --> 00:25:58.515
And now a toast

490
00:25:58.598 --> 00:26:01.226
in honor of this couple's love.

491
00:26:01.851 --> 00:26:06.106
May it flourish and serve as an example
for everyone in your lives

492
00:26:06.189 --> 00:26:07.649
now and forever.

493
00:26:09.609 --> 00:26:11.403
♪ I feel the weight now ♪

494
00:26:11.486 --> 00:26:12.612
You may share the drink.

495
00:26:12.696 --> 00:26:13.905
-Shall I?
-Yeah.

496
00:26:14.406 --> 00:26:16.658
[tender music continues]

497
00:26:17.242 --> 00:26:18.994
[officiant] Please. now join your hands.

498
00:26:19.578 --> 00:26:24.874
This cord right here
is entirely made up of delicate fibers.

499
00:26:24.958 --> 00:26:28.044
but when intertwined.
they become stronger.

500
00:26:28.128 --> 00:26:32.090
And so. in the same way.
we hope your love will strengthen

501
00:26:32.173 --> 00:26:34.843
and withstand
the hardships you'll endure

502
00:26:35.802 --> 00:26:36.886
together.

503
00:26:36.970 --> 00:26:38.346
[all cheering]

504
00:26:38.430 --> 00:26:40.015
[tender music continues]

505
00:26:45.770 --> 00:26:47.147
[music fades]

506
00:27:07.917 --> 00:27:09.294
[suspenseful music playing]

507
00:27:09.377 --> 00:27:10.503
[creaking]

508
00:27:12.297 --> 00:27:13.298
Adrián?

509
00:27:15.884 --> 00:27:16.801
Adrián?

510
00:27:24.476 --> 00:27:26.895
[uneasy music playing]

511
00:27:28.897 --> 00:27:29.773
Adrián!

512
00:27:30.273 --> 00:27:32.317
[dramatic music playing]

513
00:27:32.400 --> 00:27:33.234
No!

514
00:27:35.695 --> 00:27:36.905
No! No!

515
00:27:37.697 --> 00:27:39.240
No! Help us!

516
00:27:39.324 --> 00:27:41.201
No! Help!

517
00:27:41.284 --> 00:27:42.118
Help!

518
00:27:42.202 --> 00:27:44.454
Someone call an ambulance!

519
00:27:44.537 --> 00:27:45.622
My God!

520
00:27:46.706 --> 00:27:47.666
Adrián!

521
00:27:48.958 --> 00:27:49.793
Ángela.

522
00:27:50.293 --> 00:27:52.212
Please call an ambulance!

523
00:27:52.295 --> 00:27:53.880
[dramatic music continues]

524
00:27:53.963 --> 00:27:55.590
[Vannessa] We need an ambulance. please.

525
00:27:55.674 --> 00:27:58.635
Yes. At Riviera Esmeralda. house N.

526
00:28:03.223 --> 00:28:05.225
[Ángela sobbing]

527
00:28:08.311 --> 00:28:10.480
[Vannessa. Ángela breathing heavily]

528
00:28:10.563 --> 00:28:12.607
[Ángela] No. no. no. no. no!

529
00:28:12.691 --> 00:28:14.567
No! Help us!

530
00:28:14.651 --> 00:28:16.611
[music fades]

531
00:28:21.199 --> 00:28:23.827
-["El Parrandero" playing]
-[Silvina] Hey!

532
00:28:23.910 --> 00:28:25.662
-[laughing]
-[Silvina laughing] Whoo!

533
00:28:29.124 --> 00:28:32.877
-You look so beautiful. Mama!
-Aw. thank you. Thanks.

534
00:28:32.961 --> 00:28:34.421
[Hortensia] To the happy couple!

535
00:28:34.504 --> 00:28:37.173
[Erika] To the happy couple! Yeah!

536
00:28:37.257 --> 00:28:38.967
[all cheering]

537
00:28:39.884 --> 00:28:43.805
Hey. are you still thinking about the guy
on his boat and what he said?

538
00:28:43.888 --> 00:28:45.849
What? Of course I'm not.

539
00:28:46.516 --> 00:28:48.852
Well. regardless. I'm gonna talk to him.

540
00:28:49.436 --> 00:28:50.311
But tell me. my love.

541
00:28:50.395 --> 00:28:53.106
Do you remember anything else
from last night?

542
00:28:54.065 --> 00:28:57.610
Inti only wants more money
from the Ferrers.

543
00:28:57.694 --> 00:28:59.779
And he wants my help. That's all.

544
00:28:59.863 --> 00:29:03.867
Well. obviously.
you're not going to help him.

545
00:29:03.950 --> 00:29:05.618
You seriously think I'd help him?

546
00:29:05.702 --> 00:29:09.622
I will never forget that the Ferrers
tried to kill me multiple times.

547
00:29:09.706 --> 00:29:11.374
So I plan to stay far away from them.

548
00:29:11.458 --> 00:29:13.168
I get it. I don't want to talk about this.

549
00:29:13.251 --> 00:29:16.713
And especially not on this night
because it's our wedding.

550
00:29:18.673 --> 00:29:19.632
Mmm.

551
00:29:19.716 --> 00:29:21.718
Hey. let's get some food.

552
00:29:21.801 --> 00:29:23.803
-[chuckles] Silvi!
-[Silvina] What?

553
00:29:23.887 --> 00:29:25.889
-Come with me to the bathroom?
-[Silvina] Of course!

554
00:29:25.972 --> 00:29:26.806
One sec.

555
00:29:30.602 --> 00:29:33.021
I have to save Erika from that situation.

556
00:29:33.104 --> 00:29:34.397
-Erika!
-[Silvina] Erika!

557
00:29:34.481 --> 00:29:36.357
-[laughing]
-[Camila] Let's go to the bathroom!

558
00:29:36.441 --> 00:29:37.650
Um. one minute.

559
00:29:37.734 --> 00:29:38.651
Sure.

560
00:29:39.277 --> 00:29:40.111
Sorry.

561
00:29:40.195 --> 00:29:42.155
-[Camila] This dress.
-[Erika chuckles]

562
00:29:42.238 --> 00:29:43.531
-Can't have accidents.
-Let's go.

563
00:29:43.615 --> 00:29:45.742
[David] Hey. Zorro. come here.

564
00:29:45.825 --> 00:29:46.826
[Silvina] Oh God.

565
00:29:46.910 --> 00:29:50.955
Oh. darling. I'm so happy
you were able to recover from last night.

566
00:29:51.039 --> 00:29:52.874
No. I haven't fully recovered
from last night.

567
00:29:52.957 --> 00:29:54.542
They drugged me. I fell unconscious.

568
00:29:54.626 --> 00:29:57.504
and. actually.
I did not mention anything to David.

569
00:29:57.587 --> 00:29:59.589
but I'm getting dizzy when I'm dancing.

570
00:30:00.715 --> 00:30:03.384
Were you at least able to speak
with the guy from the sail boat?

571
00:30:03.468 --> 00:30:06.721
No. from the dance floor. I realized
his boat is no longer on the dock.

572
00:30:06.805 --> 00:30:08.306
Well then. enough.

573
00:30:09.057 --> 00:30:12.393
Enough of this convo
because there's a party happening.

574
00:30:12.477 --> 00:30:14.354
and we have much to celebrate.

575
00:30:14.437 --> 00:30:16.356
-[laughs]
-Uh-huh.

576
00:30:16.439 --> 00:30:18.483
-For example. I wanna celebrate…
-Whoo!

577
00:30:19.192 --> 00:30:21.152
…that we'll be dancing together
at the club.

578
00:30:21.236 --> 00:30:23.238
-Aw. yeah!
-Aw. yeah!

579
00:30:23.321 --> 00:30:24.614
Welcome!

580
00:30:24.697 --> 00:30:28.159
-That makes me happy. Really happy.
-I'm so. so happy. I love you guys.

581
00:30:28.243 --> 00:30:31.371
-Camila. your phone is ringing.
-Excuse me.

582
00:30:32.163 --> 00:30:34.332
INCOMING CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

583
00:30:34.415 --> 00:30:36.376
Hey. this is yesterday's number. no?

584
00:30:37.168 --> 00:30:38.294
-I'll answer it!
-No!

585
00:30:38.378 --> 00:30:40.630
Give me that. Hey. stop! Shh. stop!

586
00:30:40.713 --> 00:30:42.006
[tense music playing]

587
00:30:43.758 --> 00:30:44.592
Hello?

588
00:30:46.719 --> 00:30:47.554
Who is it?

589
00:30:48.513 --> 00:30:50.223
What is this? Why are you calling?

590
00:30:53.893 --> 00:30:55.603
All right. What's your deal. Miguel?

591
00:30:55.687 --> 00:30:59.065
I swear. if you bother me again.
I'll personally call the police.

592
00:30:59.148 --> 00:31:01.067
You fucking drugged me. asshole!

593
00:31:01.150 --> 00:31:02.318
Was it you or not?

594
00:31:03.361 --> 00:31:04.195
Hello?

595
00:31:04.779 --> 00:31:05.613
What is it?

596
00:31:05.697 --> 00:31:08.950
Did you call me just to stay silent
and not say a word or what. Miguel?

597
00:31:12.662 --> 00:31:14.539
Oh. perfect. Perfect.

598
00:31:14.622 --> 00:31:15.540
I'm headed to the dock.

599
00:31:15.623 --> 00:31:17.917
but I'm calling the police
so they can arrest you right now!

600
00:31:18.001 --> 00:31:20.003
-[Erika] No. come back here!
-[Silvina] No. wait up!

601
00:31:20.086 --> 00:31:21.296
You should leave.

602
00:31:21.379 --> 00:31:23.631
[Silvina] No. this is a bad idea.
He could be a psychopath.

603
00:31:23.715 --> 00:31:25.174
[Erika] Could be? He is a psychopath.

604
00:31:25.258 --> 00:31:27.760
And a shameless asshole
for coming here on your wedding day.

605
00:31:27.844 --> 00:31:29.220
I really need you guys to leave.

606
00:31:29.304 --> 00:31:31.097
Please stop. You have to stop.

607
00:31:31.639 --> 00:31:32.932
[sighs] Girls. please leave.

608
00:31:33.016 --> 00:31:35.727
If David asks about me.
tell him I'm talking with my mom.

609
00:31:35.810 --> 00:31:38.354
-Please let me talk to him alone.
-[Erika] Camila. listen to me!

610
00:31:38.938 --> 00:31:40.899
[dramatic music playing]

611
00:31:43.818 --> 00:31:45.153
[Silvina] Let's go get David.

612
00:31:51.534 --> 00:31:54.037
[dramatic music building]

613
00:31:57.874 --> 00:31:59.417
[dramatic music continues]

614
00:32:08.551 --> 00:32:09.802
You're so beautiful.

615
00:32:13.097 --> 00:32:14.432
I could kill you. Miguel.

616
00:32:17.185 --> 00:32:18.019
Do it then.

617
00:32:20.271 --> 00:32:22.148
I'd rather die than see
you marry that asshole.

618
00:32:23.399 --> 00:32:26.527
-Why don't you just leave and let me be?
-No. I'm not gonna leave.

619
00:32:26.611 --> 00:32:29.906
I'm not leaving until you explain to me
why you married that guy.

620
00:32:29.989 --> 00:32:32.241
You're not happy. Camila.
You don't love him. okay?

621
00:32:32.325 --> 00:32:36.287
How would you know whether or not
I'm happy? Whether I love him or not?

622
00:32:36.371 --> 00:32:38.456
-Of course I do!
-You don't. No you don't. Camila.

623
00:32:38.539 --> 00:32:41.960
What you and I had was never real.
Do you know how much I suffered with you?

624
00:32:42.043 --> 00:32:44.295
-How much goddamn pain you caused me?
-No.

625
00:32:44.379 --> 00:32:46.631
The whole time!
The crying. everything that--

626
00:32:46.714 --> 00:32:49.634
-[sobbing]
-Camila! Hey. hey.

627
00:32:53.888 --> 00:32:55.098
-Wait!
-Leave now.

628
00:32:56.307 --> 00:32:57.183
Just leave.

629
00:32:59.602 --> 00:33:00.561
What happened?

630
00:33:01.604 --> 00:33:02.689
Don't you love me?

631
00:33:05.525 --> 00:33:06.985
No. I don't love you.

632
00:33:07.694 --> 00:33:09.612
-I know you do.
-No. I don't love you!

633
00:33:09.696 --> 00:33:13.199
-I know you do. Please.
-It was a fucking match on Tinder. okay?

634
00:33:13.282 --> 00:33:15.034
-It was just a damn fling.
-Camila…

635
00:33:15.118 --> 00:33:16.911
You were just a one-night stand.
you asshole!

636
00:33:16.995 --> 00:33:19.580
-Don't say that. Cam--
-Every single thing you told me was a lie!

637
00:33:19.664 --> 00:33:21.082
Don't say that. Camila!

638
00:33:21.833 --> 00:33:22.792
Don't say that.

639
00:33:23.751 --> 00:33:25.294
You know that's not true.

640
00:33:25.378 --> 00:33:27.588
-Get lost. asshole. Right now.
-Camila.

641
00:33:27.672 --> 00:33:30.299
Because if David arrives.
he is gonna kill you.

642
00:33:30.383 --> 00:33:32.176
David? Well. I'll be right here.

643
00:33:32.260 --> 00:33:33.886
I'll be right here waiting for him.

644
00:33:33.970 --> 00:33:35.388
I'm already here. my love.

645
00:33:36.347 --> 00:33:38.725
[dramatic music playing]

646
00:33:38.808 --> 00:33:40.435
Mr. Castell.

647
00:33:40.935 --> 00:33:42.228
it's time to go.

648
00:33:42.311 --> 00:33:44.772
[dramatic music continues]

649
00:33:49.861 --> 00:33:50.945
[siren wails]

650
00:33:51.029 --> 00:33:53.281
CRIME SCENE
DO NOT CROSS

651
00:33:53.781 --> 00:33:55.450
[Ángela] Just… [crying]

652
00:33:55.533 --> 00:33:56.784
…one minute.

653
00:33:56.868 --> 00:33:58.661
I need to see him for one minute.

654
00:33:58.745 --> 00:34:00.788
Ángela. you can't see him right now.

655
00:34:00.872 --> 00:34:01.873
We have to wait.

656
00:34:02.832 --> 00:34:05.752
Mom-- Mom. we'll have time
to say goodbye to him.

657
00:34:05.835 --> 00:34:08.337
I don't want to say goodbye to him. Lucas.

658
00:34:10.506 --> 00:34:13.342
We first lost your grandfather.

659
00:34:14.677 --> 00:34:15.678
and now my brother.

660
00:34:15.762 --> 00:34:19.307
I can't do this. I can't do this.
I can't… [sobbing]

661
00:34:21.684 --> 00:34:22.935
[pensive music playing]

662
00:34:23.019 --> 00:34:24.562
[Ángela] I can't do this.

663
00:34:25.688 --> 00:34:26.898
-You lead?
-Mm-hmm.

664
00:34:26.981 --> 00:34:27.815
Okay.

665
00:34:28.316 --> 00:34:30.610
[pensive music continues]

666
00:34:32.570 --> 00:34:33.529
[Ángela] Detective.

667
00:34:34.947 --> 00:34:36.991
I need to know what happened
to my brother.

668
00:34:37.784 --> 00:34:39.827
That's why my team and I are here.

669
00:34:39.911 --> 00:34:42.246
I think it's best if you go home.

670
00:34:42.872 --> 00:34:45.208
There's nothing you can do here
for the moment.

671
00:34:45.291 --> 00:34:47.085
Mom. we need to go for Eva.

672
00:34:48.377 --> 00:34:49.504
[detective] Excuse me.

673
00:34:56.844 --> 00:35:00.014
[pensive music continues]

674
00:35:05.269 --> 00:35:06.979
[music fades]

675
00:35:07.730 --> 00:35:09.816
[Camila] David. where are you taking him?

676
00:35:09.899 --> 00:35:11.150
Don't worry. my love.

677
00:35:12.026 --> 00:35:13.444
We're just gonna take him home.

678
00:35:13.528 --> 00:35:15.071
[dramatic music playing]

679
00:35:15.154 --> 00:35:16.280
[David] Be right back.

680
00:35:18.282 --> 00:35:20.284
Captain. let's go.

681
00:35:26.457 --> 00:35:27.875
[engine starts]

682
00:35:27.959 --> 00:35:29.961
[dramatic music continues]

683
00:35:39.262 --> 00:35:40.429
[music fades]

684
00:35:42.098 --> 00:35:44.016
[upbeat music playing]

685
00:35:51.649 --> 00:35:52.692
Wow!

686
00:35:54.652 --> 00:35:56.070
Congratulations.

687
00:35:58.239 --> 00:35:59.699
You look beautiful.

688
00:36:00.491 --> 00:36:02.910
-Thought you weren't coming.
-[Inti] Well. here I am.

689
00:36:03.494 --> 00:36:05.705
I wanted to congratulate you

690
00:36:05.788 --> 00:36:10.209
and wish you a very long and happy life.

691
00:36:11.460 --> 00:36:13.838
And that this new chapter is incredible.

692
00:36:13.921 --> 00:36:15.631
surrounded by beautiful people.

693
00:36:16.591 --> 00:36:18.509
-[Camila] Cheers.
-[Inti] Cheers.

694
00:36:20.595 --> 00:36:24.265
[phone ringing]

695
00:36:24.348 --> 00:36:25.558
Oh. excuse me.

696
00:36:25.641 --> 00:36:26.475
Enjoy the night.

697
00:36:28.853 --> 00:36:29.687
Hello?

698
00:36:30.813 --> 00:36:31.731
Hello?

699
00:36:32.773 --> 00:36:34.233
[tense music playing]

700
00:36:41.657 --> 00:36:42.742
[music fades]

701
00:36:44.493 --> 00:36:46.913
If you think that facing
the truth is difficult.

702
00:36:48.122 --> 00:36:50.333
imagine what all of this means to me.

703
00:36:53.377 --> 00:36:56.380
I was sleeping with Adrián
for over five years

704
00:36:56.964 --> 00:36:58.591
not knowing he was my brother.

705
00:37:01.677 --> 00:37:03.804
We were about to get married. Ángela.

706
00:37:10.144 --> 00:37:11.979
Why did you come here tonight. Cris?

707
00:37:12.063 --> 00:37:15.024
[pensive music playing]

708
00:37:15.107 --> 00:37:16.442
Adrián asked me to.

709
00:37:20.029 --> 00:37:22.490
I think he wanted to tell me
something in person.

710
00:37:24.951 --> 00:37:26.827
Do you know what happened to my brother?

711
00:37:28.704 --> 00:37:31.999
All I know is that he was never able
to recover from all the things that…

712
00:37:34.001 --> 00:37:35.670
everything that happened to us.

713
00:37:37.713 --> 00:37:39.548
He wasn't to blame for any of it.

714
00:37:39.632 --> 00:37:41.092
[Cris sobbing]

715
00:37:44.595 --> 00:37:45.930
Nobody was. Ángela.

716
00:37:52.478 --> 00:37:54.563
I learned something when I was in prison.

717
00:37:56.357 --> 00:37:58.359
That the only way to move forward

718
00:38:00.069 --> 00:38:02.571
is accepting ourselves
just the way we are.

719
00:38:03.823 --> 00:38:05.908
But now we have to do it without him.

720
00:38:07.618 --> 00:38:11.080
[Cris breathes deeply]

721
00:38:15.835 --> 00:38:18.629
My brother loved you a lot. Cris. A lot.

722
00:38:19.714 --> 00:38:22.300
So that's why the doors to my house

723
00:38:23.134 --> 00:38:25.094
will always be open for you.

724
00:38:25.177 --> 00:38:26.429
[exhales shakily]

725
00:38:27.305 --> 00:38:28.139
Thanks.

726
00:38:29.598 --> 00:38:33.227
[upbeat music playing]

727
00:38:33.311 --> 00:38:34.520
Where are you?

728
00:38:34.603 --> 00:38:36.897
[David on phone] I'm nearby. baby.
I won't be long.

729
00:38:36.981 --> 00:38:39.692
Are you sure?
You left half an hour ago. Come on.

730
00:38:40.318 --> 00:38:42.111
I'm fine. really. Don't worry.

731
00:38:43.112 --> 00:38:43.988
I love you.

732
00:38:44.572 --> 00:38:45.698
And you? Are you okay?

733
00:38:46.407 --> 00:38:47.783
Inti is here.

734
00:38:48.534 --> 00:38:51.871
Tell Inti I need to speak with him
because I have a lot of questions to ask.

735
00:38:51.954 --> 00:38:53.205
Wait. I need you to listen.

736
00:38:53.289 --> 00:38:54.290
The thing is that

737
00:38:55.166 --> 00:38:57.835
Adrián Ferrer was found dead.

738
00:38:58.878 --> 00:39:01.130
Okay. don't worry. baby.
I'll-- I'll be right there.

739
00:39:01.213 --> 00:39:02.089
[Camila] Okay.

740
00:39:03.299 --> 00:39:06.677
I hope you learned that it's bad manners
to show up uninvited.

741
00:39:08.054 --> 00:39:09.013
What'll you do?

742
00:39:09.096 --> 00:39:10.264
[pensive music playing]

743
00:39:10.348 --> 00:39:11.390
Throw me overboard?

744
00:39:11.932 --> 00:39:13.017
Punch me in the face?

745
00:39:14.518 --> 00:39:16.062
I'm right here. Go ahead.

746
00:39:16.771 --> 00:39:18.272
Stop it. Miguel.

747
00:39:18.356 --> 00:39:20.274
Why are you here? What is this?

748
00:39:20.358 --> 00:39:21.901
You know what I want. David.

749
00:39:22.568 --> 00:39:23.819
And I'm really sorry.

750
00:39:24.653 --> 00:39:26.280
I can tell you're not a bad guy.

751
00:39:26.781 --> 00:39:28.532
but you can't do anything to stop this.

752
00:39:28.616 --> 00:39:30.201
[chuckles] Son of a bitch.

753
00:39:30.743 --> 00:39:32.370
-Seriously?
-[Miguel] Seriously.

754
00:39:32.453 --> 00:39:35.039
My feelings for Camila will never change.

755
00:39:35.122 --> 00:39:36.957
Every time I see her. I…

756
00:39:38.209 --> 00:39:40.044
-I can't control myself.
-[David] Ah.

757
00:39:40.127 --> 00:39:42.129
And that's the truth.

758
00:39:42.213 --> 00:39:44.298
I wanted you to hear that from me.

759
00:39:44.382 --> 00:39:46.967
-Here. face-to-face.
-God. dude. you're fucked up.

760
00:39:47.760 --> 00:39:48.844
You're insane. man.

761
00:39:48.928 --> 00:39:51.138
I don't want you near my family. huh?

762
00:39:53.015 --> 00:39:54.058
Can you swim?

763
00:39:55.768 --> 00:39:56.644
Get off.

764
00:39:57.228 --> 00:39:58.729
Or we'll help you. Your call.

765
00:40:00.439 --> 00:40:01.774
And who's gonna do it?

766
00:40:05.111 --> 00:40:05.945
You?

767
00:40:07.863 --> 00:40:08.823
Or this moron?

768
00:40:08.906 --> 00:40:10.699
-[Miguel grunts]
-[laughing]

769
00:40:12.785 --> 00:40:13.828
Here you go.

770
00:40:14.537 --> 00:40:17.289
[laughing]

771
00:40:24.296 --> 00:40:28.467
So. I'm gonna try and get
at least some sleep because

772
00:40:29.552 --> 00:40:32.096
tomorrow at 6:00
they give us Adrián's body.

773
00:40:32.179 --> 00:40:33.305
[inhales]

774
00:40:33.389 --> 00:40:35.099
You think Adrián was unhappy?

775
00:40:37.893 --> 00:40:38.894
[Ángela] I don't know.

776
00:40:39.437 --> 00:40:43.357
Was he so unhappy that he would actually
kill himself the day before meeting me?

777
00:40:43.441 --> 00:40:46.152
[Ángela] My brother
didn't kill himself. Cris.

778
00:40:46.235 --> 00:40:48.279
He was tied down in the pool.

779
00:40:48.362 --> 00:40:50.322
[uneasy music playing]

780
00:40:56.412 --> 00:40:57.455
[exhales]

781
00:40:59.415 --> 00:41:01.208
[Benito] Nobody escapes a heart attack.

782
00:41:02.001 --> 00:41:04.462
Not even a healthy man
with this kind of body?

783
00:41:04.545 --> 00:41:05.671
[Benito] Not even him.

784
00:41:05.754 --> 00:41:08.215
And his body was in the tub
the entire night.

785
00:41:08.299 --> 00:41:10.342
Which means we don't have
any traces of DNA.

786
00:41:11.635 --> 00:41:12.470
[sighs]

787
00:41:14.346 --> 00:41:17.057
[Benito] However.
the most recent tissue test we conducted

788
00:41:17.141 --> 00:41:19.727
indicates that he had sex
the night he died.

789
00:41:20.769 --> 00:41:22.271
And not just regular sex.

790
00:41:24.148 --> 00:41:25.941
He's got marks on his wrists.

791
00:41:26.525 --> 00:41:29.236
This man was tied up.
Most likely to the bed.

792
00:41:29.737 --> 00:41:34.200
So then. Jesús Franco meets
this mystery woman on Tinder.

793
00:41:34.783 --> 00:41:38.913
They chat for two weeks. they meet up.
they have sex. she ties him up.

794
00:41:39.497 --> 00:41:40.789
and he suffers a heart attack.

795
00:41:41.582 --> 00:41:43.792
Mmm. some luck this guy had.

796
00:41:43.876 --> 00:41:44.710
[phone chimes]

797
00:41:49.590 --> 00:41:53.594
UNKNOWN NUMBER
STILL AT RIVIERA ESMERALDA?

798
00:41:53.677 --> 00:41:57.890
I'LL WAIT FOR YOU AT HOUSE G

799
00:41:57.973 --> 00:42:00.392
[detective 1] We need to close
the report on Adrián Ferrer.

800
00:42:00.476 --> 00:42:01.393
[Benito] Okay.

801
00:42:01.477 --> 00:42:02.353
[detective 1 sighs]

802
00:42:03.229 --> 00:42:04.772
The family is waiting on it.

803
00:42:04.855 --> 00:42:08.150
They've asked for absolute discretion
with regards to the toxicology screen.

804
00:42:08.234 --> 00:42:09.401
I understand them.

805
00:42:10.361 --> 00:42:13.739
[Benito] He was inside the pool
for 24 hours before they found him.

806
00:42:19.245 --> 00:42:22.373
There was enough oxycodone
at his house to put down an elephant.

807
00:42:22.456 --> 00:42:23.290
No.

808
00:42:24.583 --> 00:42:27.670
This man did not die of
an oxycodone overdose.

809
00:42:27.753 --> 00:42:30.381
If he had. he'd display cerebral hypoxia.

810
00:42:30.464 --> 00:42:32.758
And his cause of death
was heart related too.

811
00:42:32.841 --> 00:42:35.719
This man here also died of a heart attack.

812
00:42:35.803 --> 00:42:38.305
[detective 2] And it just so happens
that he was also tied.

813
00:42:38.389 --> 00:42:40.558
[uneasy music playing]

814
00:42:40.641 --> 00:42:42.101
[uneasy music continues]

815
00:42:50.818 --> 00:42:54.405
STILL AT RIVIERA ESMERALDA?
I'LL WAIT FOR YOU AT HOUSE G

816
00:42:54.488 --> 00:43:01.078
IT'S OPEN

817
00:43:33.736 --> 00:43:34.945
I didn't expect you.

818
00:43:35.821 --> 00:43:36.989
Especially like that.

819
00:43:37.072 --> 00:43:40.242
[dramatic sting]

820
00:43:40.326 --> 00:43:41.368
[music fades]

821
00:43:41.452 --> 00:43:44.038
[seagulls squawking]

822
00:43:46.624 --> 00:43:48.917
[indistinct chatter]

823
00:43:53.130 --> 00:43:56.425
[indistinct chatter over radio]

824
00:43:56.508 --> 00:43:57.676
[camera shutter clicks]

825
00:44:01.055 --> 00:44:03.098
[pensive music playing]

826
00:44:08.771 --> 00:44:10.773
[Ángela] I need to go in.
This is this property.

827
00:44:10.856 --> 00:44:11.982
[detective 1] Detective!

828
00:44:13.025 --> 00:44:14.234
[detective 2] Let her through.

829
00:44:15.653 --> 00:44:17.738
-[Lucas] But Mom. what's--
-[Ángela sighs]

830
00:44:19.740 --> 00:44:20.741
[gasps]

831
00:44:21.784 --> 00:44:23.160
It can't be true.

832
00:44:23.243 --> 00:44:24.411
[gasps. exhales]

833
00:44:24.495 --> 00:44:25.329
It can't.

834
00:44:27.331 --> 00:44:29.041
-[detective 2] Did you know him?
-[sighs]

835
00:44:31.210 --> 00:44:32.044
Yes.

836
00:44:32.586 --> 00:44:33.754
He was my brother.

837
00:44:34.338 --> 00:44:35.297
My half-brother.

838
00:44:35.881 --> 00:44:37.132
[detective 1] Boss.

839
00:44:37.216 --> 00:44:38.217
[detective 2] What is it?

840
00:44:39.009 --> 00:44:40.386
This is the victim's phone.

841
00:44:43.389 --> 00:44:45.933
The most recent notifications
were from Tinder.

842
00:44:46.016 --> 00:44:47.476
-From Tinder?
-Yes.

843
00:44:47.559 --> 00:44:51.230
Last night. he was messaging
a profile Red Velvet.

844
00:44:51.313 --> 00:44:52.773
-I'm sorry.
-Same as Jesús Franco.

845
00:44:52.856 --> 00:44:54.316
[detective 1] And Adrián Ferrer.

846
00:44:55.484 --> 00:44:57.528
Did I hear you say Red Velvet?

847
00:44:59.822 --> 00:45:01.699
-[gasps] It's her.
-[Lucas exhales]

848
00:45:02.241 --> 00:45:04.201
[chuckling]

849
00:45:04.284 --> 00:45:05.994
[Camila] Well. maybe we should just leave.

850
00:45:06.078 --> 00:45:07.830
I'm sorry to rain on your parade.

851
00:45:07.913 --> 00:45:09.081
Good morning.

852
00:45:09.164 --> 00:45:10.791
Are you Ms. Camila Román?

853
00:45:10.874 --> 00:45:13.585
Well. yes. but it's Mrs. now. [chuckles]

854
00:45:13.669 --> 00:45:16.755
I'm a lead investigator with the CTI.
Indira Martínez.

855
00:45:16.839 --> 00:45:19.550
-This is my partner.
-Sergio Lobos. nice to meet you.

856
00:45:19.633 --> 00:45:22.261
-[Camila] How are you?
-We're gonna need you to accompany us.

857
00:45:23.178 --> 00:45:24.805
But why? Where are we going?

858
00:45:25.681 --> 00:45:27.474
May we speak for a moment?

859
00:45:27.558 --> 00:45:29.810
[dramatic music playing]

860
00:45:29.893 --> 00:45:31.645
-[woman] What's going on?
-I'll handle it.

861
00:45:31.729 --> 00:45:33.897
-[woman] Sweetie. please be careful.
-Don't worry.

862
00:45:33.981 --> 00:45:35.482
[Indira] In the past 48 hours.

863
00:45:35.566 --> 00:45:39.236
we have found three men murdered
under similar circumstances.

864
00:45:39.319 --> 00:45:41.780
The last person they all talked to

865
00:45:41.864 --> 00:45:43.031
was you.

866
00:45:43.115 --> 00:45:45.033
[dramatic music continues]

867
00:45:51.999 --> 00:45:53.792
[dramatic music continues]

868
00:48:01.587 --> 00:48:03.922
[music fades]

868
00:48:04.305 --> 00:49:04.266
